msgstr "Drop forwarded TCP/853 from LAN to non-router destinations. Can break DoT to public resolvers; use only if you accept that tradeoff."

msgid "Privacy kill switch"
msgstr "Privacy kill switch"

msgid "The glinet-privacy watchdog schedules iptables FORWARD rules. Configure WireGuard or OpenVPN in the GL.iNet admin first, then set the tunnel interface name below (often <code>wgclient</code> or <code>wg0</code>). The <strong>Overview</strong> tab shows live interface status. Stock firmware may expose a separate VPN kill switch — see the vendor section at the bottom."
msgstr "The glinet-privacy watchdog schedules iptables FORWARD rules. Configure WireGuard or OpenVPN in the GL.iNet admin first, then set the tunnel interface name below (often <code>wgclient</code> or <code>wg0</code>). The <strong>Overview</strong> tab shows live interface status. Stock firmware may expose a separate VPN kill switch — see the vendor section at the bottom."

msgid "Privacy watchdog (glinet-privacy)"
msgstr "Privacy watchdog (glinet-privacy)"

msgid "Enable watchdog"
msgstr "Enable watchdog"

msgid "If disabled, killswitch rules are flushed."
msgstr "If disabled, killswitch rules are flushed."

msgid "WireGuard interface"
msgstr "WireGuard interface"

msgid "Must match the interface name when the stock VPN client has brought WireGuard up. Check <em>Network → Interfaces</em> or run <code>ip link</code>."
msgstr "Must match the interface name when the stock VPN client has brought WireGuard up. Check <em>Network → Interfaces</em> or run <code>ip link</code>."

